Scotland’s independent schools enjoy the fame of academic excellence and this continued in 2018 with another set of outstanding exam results, further reinforced by individual and collective success in sport, art, music and other community endeavors.
With more than 30,000 students across Scotland, these schools, represented by the Scottish Council for Independent Schools (SCIS), strive to provide the highest level of service for their students and their parents.
Independent schools want to prepare their students for further and higher education, the chosen career path and the city they have as global citizens.
As the education sector that can design and implement a tailored school program, we see that modern languages are still a popular and desirable subject of choice in schools.
Nelson Mandela once said, “If you talk to a man in a language he understands, the conversation is imprinted in his memory.
