This year’s results of recent exams show that languages are at the top of the rankings with the highest levels of achievement in independent schools.
68% of the students who learned a foreign language achieved an excellent grade.
Data collected in 74 schools of the Scottish Council for Independent Schools (SCIS) showed that 72% of pupils achieved an excellent score in Mandarin, and an excellent score was also obtained by 72% of pupils of German, and 69% of pupils of French.
